features: Compatible with Quest3/Quest2/Pro/Pico4 Accessories: Syntech link cable connects your VR devices to a gaming PC so that you can play all Steam VR games, providing perfect PC VR experience. The color and design of the cable match perfectly with the Quest3, Quest2 headset.

Super Cost-effective: Syntech Link Cable combining the two advantages of length and excellent connection performance will make you feel good value for money. As a reminder, the charging current will decrease as the cable length increases, so we do not recommend using this cable to charge your Quest3/Quest2/Pro/Pico4. Additionally, to enhance your VR experience, we do not recommend using this cable when the headset is at a low battery level.

Excellent Link Performance: This cable supports USB 3.0 transmission speed. Stable and fast data synchronization working with sustained and reliable current brings you a smooth VR gaming experience. The attached velcro strap fixes the cable and headset to prevent disconnection during movement. Note: When connecting to your computer, please insert this USB 3.0 cable into the USB A 3.1/ USB A 3.0 port.

Flexible and Comfortable: This 16 ft long cable gives you maximum freedom of movement without being restricted while immersed in the VR world. At the same time, considering the users' experience, the regular USB C port is especially changed to L Shaped design to enhance customers’ comfort.

Quality Assurance and Customer Service: This link cable can bend freely without breaking by using durable materials, having good flexibility, stretch resistance, and abrasion resistance. We provide a USER GUIDE tutorial to help you smoothly enable cable link and provide solutions for some of the problems you may encounter while using wired link. In addition, Syntech provides an 18-month Warranty for hassle-free return or refund and Friendly Customer Service Support for this link cable.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 3, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Best link cable I have used so far.
reviews.reviewText: I can say for the price of this link cable and the length and durability the price is worth it straight out of the box easy connection no struggling with the headset connector and best of all it works perfectly I did buy other types of link cable before not a great experience with some especially with the connector either it's to tight or to loose and the cable is to stiff or brittle. I already had the quest link cable I didn't want to pay a whole lot for it again so I give this cable a try to my surprise it works well and connects right away my meta head set recognized it right away great experience with this cable been using it for 2 months almost every day the only down side is don't use it for charging your headset either use the charger that came with the headset or look for something else it charges really slow but overall the best for a quest link headset to pc cable I will buy another if this guy goes down but I doubt it will and I do recommend it as a good replacement for the quest link cable.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 13, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Works great, good price
reviews.reviewText: No complaints. Seems like a good quality cable. I had been using AirLink with my Quest 2 and it is fine but for fast head movements or some really detailed scenes it would get laggy. This fixes all of that for those times when I don’t need to be fully mobile. I like that it came with a Velcro strap that secures it to the headset. Overall great bargain.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 5, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars I played H3VR with this budget cable
reviews.reviewText: I have only used this for two times; on the second session, it did not work at first, but magically did after 10 minutes of waiting. Maybe it got confused if i was using air link or the cable rift. I only bought this because it's cheaper than the 80 dollar official one to play H3VR since air link doesn't work well.Anyone whos new to using a cable link can have the cord into your shirt or go behind your back so you can't whack it accidentally. It's a minor but necessary discomfortMy thing will probably break after a few months like I saw on other reviews but if you don't use vr much like me, maybe this is for you. that's why I'm rating 5 star and not three- it's cheap enough for my purposes.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 20, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Good build. Not usb 3.0
reviews.reviewText: The build quality is exceptional for the price and I’m very happy with the overall look, feel, and fit. The only issue is the data transfer speeds measured by the oculus application on my pc. With the cable plugged into my quest 3 and the “vr ready” usb 3.0 port on my motherboard the oculus application only reads 336Mbps and gives a warning saying that it is a usb2.0 connection. Despite this, the cable performs perfectly fine and I’m still able to run native resolution at 90hz. As for the charging that everyone complains about, that’s not the cables fault. Power delivery is up to your motherboard and it’s not within spec to supply as much power as this headset is going to draw. Be happy it’s still using up battery, otherwise your motherboard would blow up.
